nde2.pull.methodcalls.discovery

Class FindAreas

  • java.lang.Object
    • nde2.pull.methodcalls.BaseMethodCall
      • nde2.pull.methodcalls.discovery.DiscoveryMethodCall
        • nde2.pull.methodcalls.discovery.FindAreas

  • public class FindAreas
extends DiscoveryMethodCall
    Encapsulates the FindAreas() call to the NDE2 web service.

    Build FindAreas requests declaratively by currying, for instance: 

     new FindAreas().forPostcode(POSTCODE).ofLevelType(LEVELTYPE)
                .inHierarchy(HIERARCHY);

    The remote method only gets called when you execute() it.

    This will return a set of areas that contain POSTCODE, are of the LEVELTYPE level in hierarchy HIERARCHY. Note: The remote procedure for this is wonky. It may return objects that were not asked for (i.e. an Area of hierarchy 2 if asked for areas of hierarchy 26).

    This operation is a composite search operation which combines all the existing area searches. The postcode, area string and SNAC code are separate parameters to avoid parsing complexities. A setting of HierarchyId= 0 tells the service to use “Stats by Area” rules to pick hierarchy for level type. One of postcode, area name part and (SNAC) Code must be supplied. All other parameters optional.

    Current area search operations:

    • SearchAreaByCode(code[, hierarchyId, leveltypeid])
    • SearchAreaByNameHierarchy(name[, hierarchyid])
    • SearchAreaByNameLevelType(name, leveltypeid)
    • SearchAreaByPostcodeHierarchy(postcode[, hierarchyid])
    • SearchAreaByPostcodeLevelType(postcode, leveltypeid)
    • SearchSByAByName(name, leveltypeid)
    • SearchSByAByPostcode(postcode, leveltypeid)

        Description copied from class: BaseMethodCall
        Defines the execution plan of a call. Usually, this means plugging in a remote method name and the params into the other doCall(), however it can be used for anything, such as checking some parameters and then deciding to use a different call altogether, because the other one is utterly broken for given inputs. (Looking at you, FindAreas)

      • execute

        public java.util.Set<Area> execute()
                            throws java.io.IOException,
                                   XmlPullParserException,
                                   NDE2Exception
        This method will take data supplied to this FindAreas and call the web service. It will then parse the result, or thrown an Exception if there is a problem.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Usually occurs when a connection could not be established, or the URL called is wrong for some reason.
        XmlPullParserException - May occur if the server returns some WTF-worthy XML.
        NDE2Exception - Encapsulates an error response returned by the service itself.
        Returns:
        A set of areas returned by the service.
